# migrated from tests/cases/symbolic.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test symbolic]
# Generation 65 (sym-bench driven): symbolic-register recognition. The
# cryptic-stimulus challenge showed the LLM's first move is to NAME the register
# of a non-prose stimulus, not wall. parrot0 now classifies by structural form
# (no decoding, no hardcoded answer) and names it. Replies vary to avoid repeats,
# so these cases assert a stable opener — the second phrasing is exercised live.
> abccba
< That looks like a palindrome.
> ... --- ...
< That looks like Morse code.
> def foo(
< That looks like a snippet of code.
> h3ll0
< That looks like leetspeak.
> do re mi fa sol
< Those are musical notes (solfège).
# Numeric palindrome (spaces dropped) is still recognized from form.
> 1 2 3 2 1
< That looks like a palindrome.
# Guard: plain prose must NOT be hijacked by any recognizer — it falls through.
> the otter swims downstream
< I don't understand that yet.

